### 1) Login to obtain a JWT
POST http://localhost:8000/api/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "partner@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Save the token from the response as {{token}} in your HTTP client environment

### 2) List products (requires Bearer token)
GET http://localhost:8000/api/products
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 3) Get a product by id
GET http://localhost:8000/api/products/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 4) List your users (scoped to authenticated Client)
GET http://localhost:8000/api/users
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 5) Get a user by id (must belong to authenticated Client)
GET http://localhost:8000/api/users/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 6) Create a new user for the authenticated Client (client is set automatically)
POST http://localhost:8000/api/users
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "email": "new.user@example.com",
  "firstname": "New",
  "lastname": "User"
}

### 7) Delete a user (must belong to authenticated Client)
DELETE http://localhost:8000/api/users/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}